    "Once again, we extend η i 1 (x 1,..., x d) = η i 1 (x 1,..., x k+1).",
    "Finally, we letη i = η i 1 dx 1 ∧ • • • ∧ dx k+1.We observe that the weak * convergence of η i 1 implies also the weak * convergence η i → η insideL ∞ ([0, 1] d, k+1 R d).Since the space L ∞ cl ([0, 1] d, k+1 R d) is weak * closed, it suffices to show that each η i is closed.",
    "This follows from the definition of the exterior derivative and the fact that ∂ ∂e j η i = 0 for all j > k + 1, which is a consequence of the definition.Conjecture 1.",
    "1.11Let T be a metric d-current on R d supported inside Q = [0, 1] d. Then there exists some u ∈ L 1 (Q) such that Cd T (φ) = Q uφ dL d for all φ ∈ C ∞ c (R d).",
